M|Visi|tx|The Vision/Traction Organizer is the single most important document in EOS. It captures your company's vision on two pages by answering eight ct questions. When the leadership team is aligned on the V/TO, every decision becomes clearer, every hire becomes easier, and every meeting becomes more productive. This guide walks through each question w/ exercises, templates, and facilitation tips.
M|Tabl|tx|1. [The Eight Questions](#the-eight-questions)
M|Tabl|2. [|Core Values](#question-1-core-values)
M|Tabl|3. [|Core Focus](#question-2-core-focus)
M|Tabl|4. [|10-Year Target](#question-3-10-year-target)
M|Tabl|5. [|mk st](#question-4-mk-st)
M|Tabl|6. [|3-Year Picture](#question-5-3-year-picture)
M|Tabl|7. [|1-Year Plan](#question-6-1-year-plan)
M|Tabl|8. [|Quarterly Rocks](#question-7-quarterly-rocks)
M|Tabl|9. [|Issues List](#question-8-issues-list)
M|Tabl|tx|10. [Complete V/TO Template](#complete-vto-template)
M|Tabl|11. |CloudSync (B2B SaaS, $4M ARR)](#filled-in-vto-example-cloudsync-b2b-saas-4m-arr)
M|Tabl|tx|12. [Facilitation Tips for V/TO sn](#facilitation-tips-for-vto-sn)
M|Tabl|tx|---
M|The |The |the Vision side (questions 1-4) and the Traction side (questions 5-8). Vision defines where you are going. Traction defines how you will get there.
M|The |tx|\| Page \| Questions \| Purpose \|
M|The |tx|\|------\|-----------\|---------\|
M|The |tx|\| **Vision** \| Core Values, Core Focus, 10-Year Target, mk st \| Long-term identity and direction \|
M|The |tx|\| **Traction** \| 3-Year Picture, 1-Year Plan, Quarterly Rocks, Issues List \| Near-term execution and priorities \|
M|Ques|tx|Core values are the defining characteristics of your organization. They are not aspirational slogans posted on a wall. They describe who you truly are at your best.
M|Core|**St|gn a List (50+ Values)**
M|Core|Have|
M|Core|it|What made that person exceptional?
M|Core|it|What traits do they share w/ other top performers?
M|Core|it|What behaviors do you celebrate and reward?
M|Core|tx|Combine all lists. You shd have 40-60 qualities.
M|Core|**St|Group and Consolidate (15-20 Themes)**
M|Core|tx|Cluster similar values together. "Integrity," "honesty," and "transparency" might become one theme. Give each cluster a working label.
M|Core|**St|Debate and Narrow (3-7 Final Values)**
M|Core|For |
M|Core|it|Is this truly a core value, or is it something we wish we were?
M|Core|it|wld we fire a hi performer who consistently violated this value?
M|Core|it|wld we keep someone who embodies this value even if they underperformed for a quarter?
M|Core|it|Does this value differentiate us from cr?
M|Core|**St|Define Each Value**
M|Core|tx|Write 2-3 bullet points under each value that describe observable behaviors.
M|Core|tx|\| Core Value \| Behavioral Indicators \|
M|Core|tx|\|-----------\|----------------------\|
M|Core|tx|\| **Own It** \| Takes responsibility w/o being asked. Admits mistakes quickly. Follows through on every commitment. \|
M|Core|tx|\| **Do the Right Thing** \| Tells the truth even when it hurts. Puts the cs first. Makes ethical choices under pressure. \|
M|Core|tx|\| **Grow or Die** \| Seeks feedback actively. Reads, learns, and improves quarterly. Embraces uncomfortable challenges. \|
M|Core|**Co|**
M|Core|it|Too many values (more than 7 become impossible to remember)
M|Core|it|Aspirational values instead of actual values
M|Core|it|Generic values that cld apply to any company ("excellence," "teamwork")
M|Core|it|Not using values in hiring, firing, and rv decisions
M|Ques|Core|your purpose/cause/passion and your niche. Together, they define what you are best at and why you exist.
M|Find|Ask |
M|Find|it|Why does this company exist beyond making money?
M|Find|it|What wld the world lose if we disappeared?
M|Find|it|What gets us out of bed on the hardest days?
M|Find|tx|This is not a mission statement. It is one sentence that captures your reason for being.
M|Find|**Ex|**
M|Find|it|"To simplify small business." (Accounting SaaS)
M|Find|it|"To transform how people learn." (EdTech company)
M|Find|it|"To bd things that matter." (Engineering firm)
M|Find|Your|
M|Find|it|What can we be the best in the world at?
M|Find|it|Where do we consistently win against cr?
M|Find|it|What do cs say is uniquely valuable abt us?
M|Find|**Ex|**
M|Find|it|"Cloud accounting for small businesses" (Niche within accounting)
M|Find|it|"Mobile-first corporate training" (Niche within EdTech)
M|Find|it|"Complex structural engineering in seismic zones" (Niche within engineering)
M|Core|tx|```
M|Core|Purp|________________________________
M|Core|Nich|________________________________
M|Core|tx|```
M|Core|**Fi|** Every new opportunity, pd, or hire shd pass through your Core Focus. If it doesn't align, say no.
M|Ques|tx|The 10-Year Target is your Big, Hairy, Audacious Goal (BHAG). It shd be specific enough to measure, bold enough to inspire, and clear enough that anyone in the company can understand it.
M|BHAG|**St|** Have each leadership team member write their version independently.
M|BHAG|**St|** Share and discuss. Look for common themes.
M|BHAG|**St|** Agree on one target. It shd:
M|BHAG|it|Be a single, clear number or milestone
M|BHAG|it|Feel achievable but ambitious (60-70% confidence)
M|BHAG|it|Be measurable w/ no ambiguity
M|BHAG|it|cr energy when stated out loud
M|BHAG|**Ex|**
M|BHAG|tx|\| Company tp \| 10-Year Target \|
M|BHAG|tx|\|-------------\|---------------\|
M|BHAG|tx|\| SaaS Startup \| $100M ARR \|
M|BHAG|tx|\| Professional Services \| 500 employees across 10 offices \|
M|BHAG|tx|\| Manufacturing \| Largest custom metal fabricator east of the Mississippi \|
M|BHAG|tx|\| Agency \| Serve 1,000 brands generating $1B+ combined rv \|
M|BHAG|tx|\| Healthcare \| 50 clinics across 5 states \|
M|BHAG|**Co|**
M|BHAG|it|Making it too easy (not inspiring)
M|BHAG|it|Making it too vague ("be the best")
M|BHAG|it|Having multiple targets (pick one)
M|BHAG|it|Changing it every year (it shd be stable for a decade)
M|Ques|tx|The mk st has four parts that define how you attract and win cs.
M|Part|Defi|
M|Part|- **|** Industry, size, rv, location, title of buyer
M|Part|- **|** Attitudes, values, pain points, buying behavior
M|Part|- **|** Name 10-20 companies that perfectly represent your target mk
M|Part|tx|List three things that, taken together, differentiate you from every cr. Each unique alone may not be distinctive. The combination must be.
M|Part|tx|\| Company \| Unique 1 \| Unique 2 \| Unique 3 \|
M|Part|tx|\|---------\|----------\|----------\|----------\|
M|Part|tx|\| Accounting SaaS \| Built for non-accountants \| Same-day phone support \| Automated tax prep \|
M|Part|tx|\| Engineering Firm \| Seismic specialists \| 48-hour turnaround quotes \| In-house 3D modeling \|
M|Part|tx|\| mk Agency \| Only B2B SaaS \| perf guarantees \| Dedicated strategist \|
M|Part|tx|Name and visualize the steps a cs takes from first contact to long-term relationship. Give it a branded name.
M|Part|**Ex|"The Clarity Path"**
M|Part|tx|1. Discovery Call (30 min)
M|Part|tx|2. st Assessment (delivered in 5 days)
M|Part|tx|3. Proposal and Agreement
M|Part|tx|4. Onboarding Sprint (first 30 days)
M|Part|tx|5. Quarterly Business Reviews
M|Part|tx|6. Annual st Reset
M|Part|tx|What promise can you make that removes risk for the buyer?
M|Part|**Ex|**
M|Part|it|"Your first month free if you don't see ROI by day 30."
M|Part|it|"We'll redo any deliverable you're not satisfied w/, no questions asked."
M|Part|it|"100% money-back guarantee for the first 90 days."
M|Ques|tx|Paint a vivid picture of what the company looks like in three years. Be specific enough that everyone can visualize it.
