M|Befo|it|[ ] Book a two-day off-site away from the office
M|Befo|- [ |each leader writes their answers to all eight questions independently
M|Befo|it|[ ] Assign a facilitator (either an EOS Implementer or the Integrator)
M|Befo|- [ |phones off, laptops closed, all voices heard
M|Befo|it|[ ] Prepare a large whiteboard or flip charts
M|Duri|it|[ ] Spend Day 1 on Vision (questions 1-4), Day 2 on Traction (questions 5-8)
M|Duri|it|[ ] Allow healthy debate but enforce time limits per question
M|Duri|it|[ ] Use the "fist to five" technique for consensus (0 = strongly disagree, 5 = fully support)
M|Duri|it|[ ] If the team cannot agree after 20 minutes, the Integrator makes the call
M|Duri|it|[ ] Record every decision immediately on the V/TO document
M|Afte|it|[ ] Clean up the V/TO within 48 hours and distribute to the leadership team
M|Afte|it|[ ] Schedule a company-wide meeting to share the V/TO within 30 days
M|Afte|it|[ ] rv the V/TO at every quarterly sn
M|Afte|it|[ ] up it formally at the annual planning sn
M|Afte|it|[ ] Post it visibly in the office (or pin it in a shared digital workspace)
M|Comm|tx|\| Pitfall \| What Happens \| How to Fix \|
M|Comm|tx|\|---------\|-------------\|------------\|
M|Comm|tx|\| Visionary dominates \| Team agrees to avoid conflict \| Facilitator calls on each person directly \|
M|Comm|tx|\| al paralysis \| No decisions made \| Time-box each question, Integrator breaks ties \|
M|Comm|tx|\| Too abstract \| V/TO reads like a philosophy paper \| Force specific numbers and dates for every section \|
M|Comm|tx|\| Rushed process \| Leadership doesn't internalize \| Spend the full two days, no shortcuts \|
M|Comm|tx|\| No follow-through \| V/TO sits in a drawer \| rv quarterly, reference in every Level 10 meeting \|